%% Diagram: Linearizable timeline — operations as wall-clock intervals with linearization points
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Client A
    participant K as Key x (linearization)
    participant B as Client B
    participant C as Client C

    A->>K: write(x=1) start
    Note over K: lin point: x = 1
    K-->>A: ack
    B->>K: read(x) start
    K-->>B: returns 1
    A->>K: read(x) start
    K-->>A: returns 1
    B->>K: write(x=2) start
    Note over K: lin point: x = 2
    K-->>B: ack
    C->>K: read(x) start
    K-->>C: returns 2
    Note over A,C: Real-time order: A:write(1) < B:read(1) < B:write(2) < C:read(2)
